item.title: CVE-2018-14664|2024-08-05T09:38:12.688Z -- %5Bunknown%5D -- foreman
item.description: A flaw was found in foreman from versions 1.18. A stored cross-site scripting vulnerability exists due to an improperly escaped HTML code in the breadcrumbs bar. This allows a user with permissions to edit which attribute is used in the breadcrumbs bar to store code that will be executed on the client side.
